@$VER: MTG.guide 2.12 dec.97


@node ENDU1 "Enduring Renewal/ Fallen Angel/ Ornithopter
@{" " link MTG_COMBO.guide/ENDUR}

 @{b}Enduring Renewal/ Fallen Angel/ Ornithopter@{ub}


  The Enduring Renewal is a card which isn't used by many
  players we know because of it's nasty side affect (you
  must discard all creature cards you draw). We hope more
  people start using the Enduring Renewal after reading
  this combo explanation.

  When you have all three cards of this combo on the table
  you can sacrifice your Ornithopter to your Fallen Angel
  which costs you exactly 0 mana and your  Fallen Angel
  gets +2/+1 and your Ornithopter goes to your graveyard
  but thanks to your Enduring Renewal the Ornithopter goes
  back to your hand, wich goes automatic, fortunately the
  Ornithopter has a casting cost of 0 so you can put it
  directly under play again, than when your Ornithopter has
  just settled on your playing ground sacrifice it again and
  it starts all over again. After you've sacrificed your
  Ornithopter a zillion times you may attack with your Angel
  and it will deal ... ehrm a lot of dammage (just pray your
  opponent hasn't got an Reverse damage or a Fog or something
  or else you've got to use this combo again).

  @{b}NOTE@{ub}: You can use any other (Artifact) Creature with
        a castig cost of 0 to replace the Ornithopter.

@endnode         
@node ENDU2 "Enduring Renewal/ Ashnod's Altar/ Carrion Ants/ Ornithopter"
@{" " link MTG_COMBO.guide/ENDUR}

 @{b}Enduring Renewal/ Ashnod's Altar/ Carrion Ants/ Ornithopter@{ub}


  This is a rather large combo it needs 4 different cards to work,
  but when it works you will be almost certain to be victorious.
  this combo is almost simular to the:
  @{"Enduring Renewal/ Fallen Angel/ Ornithopter" link ENDU1} combo, to get a
  slight idea of how the Enduring Renewal combo works, you may read
  this one first before you start reading this combo, 

  Well if you've read the "Enduring Renewal/ Fallen Angel/ Ornithopter"
  combo, this piece of text is almost useless to you but for those who
  didn't read it here comes the explanaition.

  With all four cards on the table you start off by sacrificing your
  Ornithopter to your Ashnod's Altar so you get 2 collerless mana ,the
  Ornithopter goes , thanks to your Enduring Renewal, to your hand.
  Then you can repeat this process by summoning your Ornithopter over
  and over again and sacrificing it over and over again till you've
  got about a quarter of a million collorles mana in your mana pool.
  Then you may pump up Your Carrion Ants so they become 250000/250001
  and then you may try and crush your opponent.

  @{b}NOTE@{ub}: You can use any other (Artifact) Creature with
        a castig cost of 0 to replace the Ornithopter.

  @{b}NOTE@{ub}: You can replace the Carrion Ants with an
        Fireball, Howl from Beyond, Disintegrate, etc...
@endnode
@node ENDU3 "Enduring Renewal/ Hell's Caretaker"
@{" " link MTG_COMBO.guide/ENDUR}

  @{b}Enduring Renewal/ Hell's Caretaker@{ub}


   This is the third Enduring Renewal combo sended by Luc Perrin and
   again this is a verry powerfull combo, it might not be as
   devastating as his two previous combos but this one will let your
   opponent swet just as hard, because with this combo you can get
   your dead creatures back at minimum cost.

   When you have the three cards on table, sacriface your Ornithopter
   your Hell's Caretaker and return your most powerfull creature in
   your graveyard into play. The ornithopter goes to your hand and
   you can repeat the combo a few times more till your graveyard
   has no more creatures in it.

   When you draw a creature card you'll have to discard it ( Thanks to
   your Enduring Renewal ), but you can get the creature into play
   by using the combo as above. The only miner in this combo is that
   you must tap your Hell's Caretaker to use this combo, so you can
   use this combo only once each turn.

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: You can use any other (Artifact) Creature with
        a castig cost of 0 to replace the Ornithopter.

@endnode
@node ENDU4 "Enduring Renewal/ Atog/ Ornithopter"
@{" " link MTG_COMBO.guide/ENDUR}

  @{b}Enduring Renewal/ Atog/ Ornithopter@{ub}


   At last, this is what you were all waiting for, a combo wich has
   not been sended by Luc Perrin. This one was made up by Roger and
   Robert in less than 10 seconds after seeing the three Enduring
   Renewal combos sended by Luc Perrin.

   This combo is a clone of the first two Enduring Renewal combos
   so if you want to see the first combo you may click @{" here " link ENDU1}
   and if you want to see the second combo click @{" here " link ENDU2}

   The explanation of the combo is again quite easy. First try
   and get the three cards involved on the table. Then you
   sacrifice your Ornithopter ( which returns to your hand thanks to
   your Enduring Renewal ) to your Atog and the Atog miraculously
   gets +2/+2 and has turned into a 3/4 creature. Your opponent isn't
   frightened by that, but his mood changes when you repeat this
   combo twenty times and your tiny little 1/2 Atog has grown
   to an enormous 41/42 creature just by eating a few Ornithopters.

@endnode
@node MULTI1 "Royal Assassin / Icy Manipulator / Norrit
@{" " link MTG_COMBO.guide/MAIN}

 @{b}Royal Assassin / Icy Manipulator / Norrit@{ub}


   Everybody knows the combinations:

                     Royal Assassin / Icy Manipulator
                                   ,
                         Royal Assassin / Norrit
                                 and
                        Norrit / Icy Manipulator


   But why don't you combine the three cards so you'll get a very
   powerfull triangle, because of the fact that it doesn't matter
   if one of the cards gets destroyed because the two remaining cards
   are still a combo.
   For instance, someone kills your Norrit  --> Tap a creature with
   your Icy Manipulator and destroy it with your Royal Assassin.
   Maybe someone pulverises your Icy Manipulator  --> Use your
   Norrit to let a creature attack and destroy the creature with your
   Royal Assassin.
   Someone can even kill your Royal Assassin  --> Tap a creature with
   your Icy Manipulator and let that creature attack with your Norrit
   but unfortunately it is tapped, so it gets destroyed.
   Now thats a triangle isn't it?

@endnode
@node THICK1 "Thickit Basilisk / Lure
@{" " link MTG_COMBO.guide/MAIN}

 @{b}Thickit Basilisk / Lure@{ub}


   This combo doesn't need an explanation because its to easy.
   Find this one out for yourself.
   In fact I wonder why you clicked on the @{bg highlight}@{b}X@{ub}@{bg background} in the first place.
   


   @{i}for those who really don't have a clue, here's a little explanation:@{ui}

           @{b}PUT THE LURE ON THE THICKIT BASILISK AND ATTACK.@{ub}
@endnode
